    {
      "type": "grammarRule",
      "id": "rule_nagara",
      "pattern": [
        {
          "label": "VERB (stem)",
          "color": "verb",
          "text": "[Verb ます-stem]"
        },
        {
          "label": "CONNECTOR",
          "color": "connector",
          "text": "ながら"
        },
        {
          "label": "MAIN ACTION",
          "color": "predicate",
          "text": "[Main action]"
        }
      ],
      "meaning": "While doing X, [do Y]",
      "explanation": "ながら expresses two actions happening simultaneously by the SAME subject. Attach ながら to the ます-stem (the い-row form before ます) of the SECONDARY (background) action. The main (primary) action comes in the main clause at the end. Formation: godan verbs shift the final う to the い-row; ichidan verbs drop る only.",
      "notes": [
        "The MAIN action comes LAST in the sentence. ながら marks the background / secondary action.",
        "Both actions must have the SAME subject. ながら cannot be used when different people perform the two actions.",
        "Common mistake: using て-form instead of ます-stem. 聞きながら (correct) vs. 聞いてながら (wrong)."
      ],
      "examples": [
        {
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "音楽を",
              "role": "object",
              "gloss": "music (object: を)",
              "tokens": [
