    {
      "type": "grammarRule",
      "id": "rule_tari",
      "pattern": [
        {
          "label": "VERB",
          "color": "verb",
          "text": "[Verb plain past]"
        },
        {
          "label": "+り",
          "color": "connector",
          "text": "り"
        },
        {
          "label": "VERB",
          "color": "verb",
          "text": "[Verb plain past]"
        },
        {
          "label": "+り",
          "color": "connector",
          "text": "り"
        },
        {
          "label": "CLOSING VERB",
          "color": "predicate",
          "text": "する"
        }
      ],
      "meaning": "Do things like X and Y (non-exhaustive list)",
      "explanation": "～たり～たりする lists a SAMPLE of actions among several — the list is intentionally incomplete. Formation is identical to the plain past (た-form) but replace た/だ with たり/だり. The same godan euphonic sound changes apply (く→いた→いたり, ぬ→んだ→んだり, etc.). The pattern closes with する (plain) or します / しました (polite present / past).",
      "notes": [
        "The sound changes are EXACTLY the same as for plain past — the only difference is the ending: た→たり, だ→だり.",
        "～たりする implies the list is NOT complete: テレビを見たり、本を読んだりします implies 'among other things'.",
        "You can list a single action for 'occasionally doing X': 時々、映画を見たりします (I occasionally do things like watch movies — implying other activities too)."
      ],
      "examples": [
